Actress Stephanie Okereke-Linus has welcomed a second child with her hubby, Idahosa Linus. The film director and model shared the big news on Tuesday via her Instagram page as she expressed immense gratitude to God for the arrival of their prince. The mother of two wrote: “A Princely Arrival. With thanksgiving and gratitude to our Heavenly Father, we are delighted to share with you the announcement of the birth of our second son whose arrival has immersed us with unspeakable joy.   Firm thrills guests at 2022 AMVCA     Stop shaving your pubic hairs, Blessing CEO advises ladies     My EFCC arrest God’s plan, says Naira Marley   “Indeed, the Lord has blessed us beyond measure and our hearts are filled with eternal gratitude. Glory be to His name. Stephanie & Linus. #baby #thankful #newbaby.” The couple got married on April 21, 2012 in a fairytale yet private wedding at the magnificent Abbaye de Cerray in Paris. The ceremony, which was officiated by Pastor Johnson Suleman, was exclusively by invitation as such it was attended by close friends, family and scores of movie stars. The couple welcomed their first child, Maxwell Enosata Linus in 2015.